HEADWORD: Tensible
<hw>Ten"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Tense</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Capable of being extended or
drawn out; ductile; tensible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gold . . . is likewise the most flexible and
<qex>tensible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tensile</ent>⟦br⟧
